Firſt, I ſay, that the Myſtery of the Goſpel, or of God, is Chriſt in us the hope of glory; the glory, is God in mans fleſh, Zach. 2.5. Chriſt in us, is God

manifeſt in our fleſh as in his;
                  Joh. 14.20. Chriſt in us is called the hope of glory, becauſe they in whom Chriſt is revealed, have the glory ſo revealed in them, as to wait for it in themſelves, as 'twas in him when raiſed from the dead.
